## IZMIR FISH PRICES DATASET COMMENTS

This data set contains the values of seafood in a specific date range.
If we look at average prices, the most expensive category is fish. Although imported, the cheapest type is frozen products.
The most variable product group is aquaculture, followed by fish.
The season with the highest price volatility seems to be autumn.

VOLATILITY-CATEGORY:
```{r}

balik_hal_fiyatlari%>%mutate(DEGISIM = AZAMI_UCRET- ASGARI_UCRET)%>% group_by(MAL_TURU) %>%
  summarise(across(c(DEGISIM),mean, na.rm=TRUE))%>% arrange(desc(DEGISIM))
plot_vol<- balik_hal_fiyatlari%>%mutate(DEGISIM = AZAMI_UCRET- ASGARI_UCRET)%>% group_by(MAL_TURU) %>%
  summarise(across(c(DEGISIM),mean, na.rm=TRUE))%>% arrange(desc(DEGISIM))
ggplot(plot_vol,aes(x=reorder(MAL_TURU,-DEGISIM),y=DEGISIM)) + geom_bar(stat="identity",aes(fill=MAL_TURU))
```
AVERAGE PRICE-CATEGORY:
```{r}
balik_hal_fiyatlari%>%mutate(ORTALAMA_FIYAT=((AZAMI_UCRET+ASGARI_UCRET)/2))%>%group_by(MAL_TURU) %>% summarise(across(c(ORTALAMA_FIYAT), mean, na.rm= TRUE))%>% 
  arrange(desc(ORTALAMA_FIYAT))
plot_exp<- balik_hal_fiyatlari%>%mutate(ORTALAMA_FIYAT=((AZAMI_UCRET+ASGARI_UCRET)/2))%>%group_by(MAL_TURU) %>% summarise(across(c(ORTALAMA_FIYAT), mean, na.rm= TRUE)) 
ggplot(plot_exp, aes(x=reorder(MAL_TURU, -ORTALAMA_FIYAT), y= ORTALAMA_FIYAT)) + geom_bar(stat="identity", aes(fill=MAL_TURU))
```
SEASON-VOLATILITY:
```{r}
plot_bal<-balik_hal_fiyatlari %>% mutate(AY=lubridate::month(TARIH)) %>%
  mutate(TARIH_MEVSIM=case_when(AY<=10 & AY>=9 ~"GUZ",  AY <=8 & AY >=6 ~ "YAZ",  AY<=5 & AY>=3 ~"ILKBAHAR", AY<3 ~ "KIS"), DEGISIM = AZAMI_UCRET- ASGARI_UCRET)%>%
  group_by(TARIH_MEVSIM)%>% summarise(ORTALAMA_DEGISIM=mean(DEGISIM))
plot_bal
ggplot(plot_bal,aes(x=reorder(TARIH_MEVSIM,ORTALAMA_DEGISIM),y=ORTALAMA_DEGISIM)) + geom_bar(stat="identity",aes(fill=TARIH_MEVSIM))
```



